# Firewalls:

Firewall is basically a guard that checks your data packets and can manipulate them according to your command, acts like a barrier between your computer(trusted place) and internet(untrusted place)


## How does firewalls works?

It checks each data packet before allowing them inside.
It follows a set of rules to decide which is to allows in and who to block.
If a visitor (data packet) is suspicious, then firewall blocks them.


* Firewalls can be classified in three categories :
  Traditional packet filterss, stateul filters and application gateways


